docs.abstract: The investigation is the latest hurdle for Amazon and other American tech giants as European policy makers pursue antitrust, tax and other inquiries.

docs.lead_paragraph: In the digital world, things change in an instant. One minute you are the people’s champion. In the next, perhaps a villain.

headline.main: Amazon’s E-Books Business Investigated by European Antitrust Regulators
headline.print_headline: Amazon’s E-Book Business Being Investigated in Europe

byline.original: By David Streitfeld and Mark Scott

docs.abstract: Amazon on Tuesday afternoon joined other major retailers such as Walmart, Sears and eBay and banned the sale of merchandise bearing the Confederate battle flag.
docs.snippet: Amazon on Tuesday afternoon joined other major retailers such as Walmart, Sears and eBay and banned the sale of merchandise bearing the Confederate battle flag.
docs.lead_paragraph: The debate over the Confederate battle flag has spilled into the world of commerce as major retailers including Walmart, Sears and eBay have banned the sale of merchandise bearing the Civil War symbol.

headline.main: Retailers Ban Sale of Merchandise Bearing Confederate Flag
